  "title": "CLASS 3 DRIVER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Drive Class 3 vehicles to transport goods, documents, or passengers safely and on time while maintaining vehicle condition and following safety regulations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive Class 3 vehicles (cars, vans, light goods vehicles up to 3,000 kg) safely and responsibly to assigned locations</li><li>Transport goods, documents, or passengers according to delivery schedules</li><li>Load and unload items as required to support delivery operations</li><li>Perform basic vehicle checks including fuel level, tyre condition, lights, and cleanliness to ensure vehicle readiness</li><li>Maintain vehicle cleanliness and good working condition through regular upkeep</li><li>Follow traffic laws, company Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), and safety regulations to ensure compliance and safety</li><li>Plan and adjust routes efficiently to avoid traffic delays and meet delivery timelines</li><li>Complete delivery records, trip logs, and delivery orders accurately and promptly</li><li>Report any accidents, traffic offences, or vehicle issues immediately to the appropriate personnel</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Valid Singapore Class 3 Driving Licence</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Familiarity with Singapore roads and GPS/navigation apps to optimize route planning</li><li>Basic communication skills in English or Mandarin to interact effectively during deliveries</li><li>Clean driving record preferred to demonstrate responsible driving history</li><li>Ability to work flexible hours as needed to meet delivery demands</li></ul>",
